{
  "message": "Noscript fallback on bench pages \u2014 explain JS is required\n\nWith JS disabled the playground and RPC bench just sit there forever\n(the run logic is in main.ts modules). New <noscript> banner at the\ntop of each bench page explains JS is required for that page and\npoints the visitor at the static pages (landing, honest comparison,\nwire inspector) that work fine without JS.\n\nVerified: rendered text contains \"JavaScript is required\" when\nplaywright launches a JS-disabled context against /playground.html\nand /rpc.html.\n\nInline styles on the banner because <noscript> blocks all <script>-\nloaded styles too \u2014 keeping the warning visually styled meant going\ninline. Stays consistent with the orange .lose colour the rest of\nthe site uses for honest \"this is a downside\" framing.",
  "files": [
